Great place to leave “hangry” before a show.  Stopped by here on the way to Brooklyn Steel for a quick bite and a drink.  Ordered a pretzel and chips and guacamole. I explained we were trying to make a show.  After 20 minutes I asked if our order was processed. Trying to get to the venue.  The guy at the bar gives me a attitude.  “You’ll get your food you have to wait, We only have one person in the kitchen.”  After 40 minutes we left.  It shouldn’t take 40 minutes to get guacamole & chips and a pretzel.  We gave up and walked out, a drag since we paid in advance...

One Stop Beer Shop is the gem bar of the neighborhood. Never have I been welcomed into a bar like this before. Their rotating draft list is tastefully curated, they have an immense collection of canned beers (join the Beer Society to try 40 from around the world), and there is free popcorn! I usually come here to watch baseball and football, but gladly come here to have a cozy night on other days.  It’s sometimes a bit busy when a show is going on at Brooklyn Steel, but they manage the crowd very well. The staff is very attentive, kind, and friendly.  One Stop is the best bar in the neighborhood hands down, if not northern Brooklyn.
